WEBVTT

00:01.501 --> 00:02.501
[ Mouse squeaks ]

00:02.536 --> 00:04.236
[ Penguins chirp ]

00:04.838 --> 00:05.804
[ Screeches ]

00:05.839 --> 00:08.207
[ All cheering ]

00:10.010 --> 00:10.976
[ Screeches ]

00:11.011 --> 00:12.978
[ Quacks ]

00:13.013 --> 00:14.079
¶ Adventure time ¶

00:14.114 --> 00:15.414
¶ Come on, grab your friends ¶

00:15.449 --> 00:18.183
¶ We're going to
a very distant land ¶

00:18.218 --> 00:20.752
¶ With Jake the dog
and Finn the human ¶

00:20.787 --> 00:22.220
¶ The fun will never end ¶

00:22.255 --> 00:24.556
¶ It's adventure time ¶

00:26.359 --> 00:29.361
¶¶

00:35.035 --> 00:39.004
Oh...bananas.

00:39.039 --> 00:41.339
Bananas.

00:41.374 --> 00:44.543
BMO, it's your turn
to say "bananas."

00:44.578 --> 00:48.847
There is a strange cloud
following us.

00:48.882 --> 00:50.348
Come and see.

00:50.383 --> 00:52.784
I'm too comfortable
to move.

00:52.819 --> 00:54.086
Can you just
describe it?

00:54.121 --> 00:55.754
Forget the cloud.

00:55.789 --> 00:57.422
Tell us a story instead.

00:57.457 --> 01:01.059
A nice campfire
bedtime story.

01:01.094 --> 01:03.528
Once upon a time,
there was this...

01:03.563 --> 01:07.365
cool guy and a banana
with sunglasses.

01:07.400 --> 01:08.900
Please, no.

01:08.935 --> 01:11.203
Literally
anything but bananas.

01:11.238 --> 01:14.806
Once upon a time,
there was a...

01:14.841 --> 01:17.476
bandana with sunglasses.

01:17.511 --> 01:19.144
Eh?

01:20.914 --> 01:23.148
[ Both snoring ]

01:23.183 --> 01:26.618
Good night, bed.

01:26.653 --> 01:30.155
Good night, weird cloud.

01:30.190 --> 01:33.192
Good night, weird orb.

01:35.028 --> 01:37.196
[ Snoring ]

01:38.465 --> 01:40.665
-Hey, Jake home.
[ Applause ]

01:40.700 --> 01:43.668
-Hey, Joshua home too!
[ Applause ]

01:43.703 --> 01:45.103
Whatcha doing, Dad?

01:45.138 --> 01:46.138
Scrambling eggs?

01:46.173 --> 01:48.440
Yes,
in the refrigerator!

01:48.475 --> 01:49.975
[ Laughter ]

01:50.010 --> 01:52.010
Oh, boy.

01:52.045 --> 01:53.578
I can see
where this is going.

01:53.613 --> 01:56.448
[ Laughter ]

01:57.317 --> 01:58.917
Man, that got old quick.

01:58.952 --> 02:00.585
What's going on here,
Jermaine?

02:00.620 --> 02:02.687
Wha -- wha --
what do you think?

02:02.722 --> 02:04.156
It's a dream, dum-dum.

02:04.191 --> 02:05.790
Oh, right.

02:05.825 --> 02:07.492
'Cause dream bro times.

02:07.527 --> 02:09.628
And 'cause
we burned this place down.

02:09.663 --> 02:11.363
Last year.

02:11.398 --> 02:14.633
Anyway,
what's up, Jermaine?

02:14.668 --> 02:17.302
Fine.

02:17.337 --> 02:20.105
What do you think all these
blank canvasses represent?

02:20.140 --> 02:22.440
These are,
um, mine actually.

02:22.475 --> 02:25.977
I've really been getting into
landscape painting.

02:26.012 --> 02:28.346
Mostly, like, forests
and seascapes.

02:28.381 --> 02:30.649
Strictly
representational art.

02:30.684 --> 02:31.950
Dude, that's awesome!

02:31.985 --> 02:34.653
We should collab on
an interdisciplinary performance

02:34.688 --> 02:35.654
or something.

02:35.689 --> 02:38.356
Ah, that's not really my scene,
man.

02:38.391 --> 02:40.792
I'm into real things.

02:40.827 --> 02:43.262
[ Snoring ]

02:44.564 --> 02:46.131
I'm flying!

02:46.166 --> 02:48.800
No more walking for this guy.

02:48.835 --> 02:49.968
You hear that dudes?

02:50.003 --> 02:51.536
You're retired.

02:51.571 --> 02:54.172
Just gonna float around
like a chubby bat.

02:54.207 --> 02:55.507
Water Nymph:
Hey, Finn.

02:55.542 --> 02:58.543
I made these cloud sculptures
for you.

02:58.578 --> 02:59.811
Yes!

02:59.846 --> 03:02.547
Flying Finn will never
miss out on anything.

03:02.582 --> 03:05.150
People will be all,
"Too bad Finn's not here."

03:05.185 --> 03:07.919
And I'll be like,
"Look up, surface dorks."

03:07.954 --> 03:10.556
[ Disco music plays ]

03:19.532 --> 03:20.498
Director!

03:20.533 --> 03:23.668
Where are
your accessories?

03:23.703 --> 03:27.105
Let's get the director's
accessories, please?

03:27.140 --> 03:30.108
Okay, time for the show!

03:30.143 --> 03:32.344
[ Applause ]

03:32.379 --> 03:36.181
We never have any fun
when BMO's not here.

03:36.216 --> 03:38.283
All we do is hit things.

03:38.318 --> 03:40.685
[ Laughter ]

03:40.720 --> 03:43.255
I love art.

03:47.227 --> 03:49.561
Okay, boys,
I got a job for you.

03:50.630 --> 03:53.131
Think you can handle it?
Of course you can.

03:55.735 --> 03:57.802
Now, dig.

03:57.837 --> 03:59.571
Jake: Yeah, okay.

04:02.075 --> 04:03.708
Why are we doing this,
Papa?

04:03.743 --> 04:06.111
Never you mind!

04:06.146 --> 04:07.913
Dig.

04:12.852 --> 04:14.052
[ Thumping ]

04:14.087 --> 04:16.554
[ Sighing ]
Man, I'm out of shape.

04:16.589 --> 04:19.258
I can hear my own heart
palpitating.

04:21.995 --> 04:23.395
Jeepers creepers.

04:23.430 --> 04:25.330
Don't mind that.
Just dig faster.

04:25.365 --> 04:28.133
Dig faster,
you dew droppers!

04:33.606 --> 04:36.441
Brrr!

04:37.711 --> 04:39.311
Hey, it's PB.

04:40.680 --> 04:42.580
Finn,
what are you up to?

04:42.615 --> 04:45.650
Oh, nothing.
Just using my power of flight!

04:45.685 --> 04:49.321
It's scientifically impossible
for a human boy to fly.

04:49.356 --> 04:51.523
You're gonna wish it was
scientifically possible

04:51.558 --> 04:53.625
to put those words
back in your mouth.

04:53.660 --> 04:54.659
Look!

04:54.694 --> 04:55.960
Huuup!

04:55.995 --> 04:57.595
Huuup!
Grrr.

04:57.630 --> 04:58.763
Huuup!

04:58.798 --> 05:01.099
Stop holding me back!

05:01.134 --> 05:04.703
[ Thunder crashes ]

05:04.738 --> 05:06.137
Huh?

05:06.172 --> 05:07.272
Aah!

05:07.307 --> 05:08.907
Finn, what are these?

05:12.178 --> 05:13.912
Aaaaahhhh!

05:15.215 --> 05:17.282
I'm bored.

05:17.317 --> 05:20.652
I'm boring.

05:21.855 --> 05:25.257
There's only one person
who can save this play.

05:25.825 --> 05:27.292
-Yay, he's here!
-Yay, he's here!

05:27.327 --> 05:28.460
BMO!            BMO!

05:28.495 --> 05:30.829
[ Applause ]
-A bootleg BMO?

05:30.864 --> 05:33.231
I'm bad!

05:33.266 --> 05:37.836
But you still like me.

05:37.871 --> 05:39.003
Boo!

05:39.038 --> 05:40.705
This show is terrible!

05:40.740 --> 05:43.908
I want to
talk to the director.

05:43.943 --> 05:46.678
The director is right this way,
director.

05:49.549 --> 05:52.650
Director, the director's here
to see you.

05:52.685 --> 05:55.587
Listen, the play
started out good,

05:55.622 --> 05:58.323
but it didn't have
any relatable characters.

05:58.358 --> 06:00.158
[ Gasping ] Football!

06:00.193 --> 06:02.060
I'm not Football.

06:02.095 --> 06:03.194
Oh, good.

06:03.229 --> 06:07.933
I'm AMO!

06:08.968 --> 06:11.436
Oh, bad!

06:14.441 --> 06:16.341
[ Digging ]

06:16.376 --> 06:18.843
[ Shovels clanging ]

06:18.878 --> 06:20.912
The heck!

06:20.947 --> 06:22.580
Dad,
the hole is gone!

06:22.615 --> 06:24.382
-Boys?
-Dad?

06:24.417 --> 06:25.750
Joshua:
Boys, the hole is gone!

06:25.785 --> 06:27.419
Looks like you buried me.
Why'd you do it?

06:27.454 --> 06:29.554
Aah! Dig!       Aah! Dig!

06:33.426 --> 06:35.660
Mom.            Mom.

06:38.231 --> 06:39.798
What are you doing?

06:39.833 --> 06:41.533
Mm.

06:41.568 --> 06:43.535
I'm sure this is all
really symbolic,

06:43.570 --> 06:46.037
but it's dang comfy.

06:46.072 --> 06:47.138
[ Gasping ]

06:47.173 --> 06:49.307
[ Slurping ]

06:49.342 --> 06:51.209
I don't like
where this is headed.

06:51.244 --> 06:52.944
I'm out of here.

06:53.746 --> 06:54.946
Ohhh.

06:54.981 --> 06:59.083
Mom, Dad....

06:59.118 --> 07:01.820
[ Whimpering ]

07:06.192 --> 07:09.427
How does it look?

07:09.462 --> 07:11.229
I think it looks cool.

07:11.264 --> 07:13.398
Nice.

07:13.433 --> 07:15.801
Oh!

07:17.437 --> 07:20.672
¶¶

07:23.276 --> 07:26.244
What the plop?

07:26.279 --> 07:28.446
-Help...
-Jake?

07:28.481 --> 07:30.448
Jake:
I'm aging up here!

07:30.483 --> 07:32.417
Okay, bird thoughts, Finn.

07:32.452 --> 07:35.787
Eggs, nest, wings, worms!

07:40.026 --> 07:41.092
Jake?

07:41.127 --> 07:42.527
Jake?

07:43.229 --> 07:44.195
Jake!

07:44.230 --> 07:46.264
Finn....

07:46.299 --> 07:47.966
[ Coughs ]

07:48.001 --> 07:49.934
I'm old.

07:49.969 --> 07:52.670
[ BMO cries ]

07:52.705 --> 07:55.474
Now it's too relatable!

07:58.645 --> 08:00.979
Cool, backup skin.

08:02.749 --> 08:04.716
-Aah!
-That's not what I wrote!

08:04.751 --> 08:06.618
Huh?

08:06.653 --> 08:09.187
I really respect that
you do your own stunts.

08:09.222 --> 08:11.356
You're brother's gonna
have to step up his game

08:11.391 --> 08:12.790
to keep up with you.

08:12.825 --> 08:15.126
We have to do something
about these crow's-feet,

08:15.161 --> 08:17.962
or everyone's gonna know
you're too old to play Jake.

08:17.997 --> 08:19.130
But I am Jake.

08:19.165 --> 08:21.633
[ Hissing ]

08:21.668 --> 08:23.401
What's he saying?

08:23.436 --> 08:24.869
Your lines.

08:24.904 --> 08:27.138
Hss, hss, shss, shss.
Hss, hss, shss, shss.

08:27.173 --> 08:29.807
Uh, hss, sshs, hss.

08:29.842 --> 08:32.010
Hss, hss,<i> shss,</i> shss.

08:32.045 --> 08:34.179
Just read the cue cards.

08:36.349 --> 08:37.815
BMO:
It's just a rehearsal,

08:37.850 --> 08:40.184
but it's not okay
to be really bad.

08:40.219 --> 08:42.320
BMO?
What are you doing here?

08:42.355 --> 08:44.022
This is my nightmare!

08:44.057 --> 08:45.924
-No, this is my --
-No, this is my --

08:45.959 --> 08:48.192
Oh,<i> our</i> nightmares,
I guess.

08:48.227 --> 08:49.494
And you're here with us.

08:49.529 --> 08:50.762
[ Rumbling ]
-I am?

08:50.797 --> 08:53.398
The unconscious
is so complicated.

08:53.433 --> 08:56.501
Ahh!
Ahh!            Ahh!

08:56.536 --> 08:57.502
Bird thoughts!

08:57.537 --> 08:59.571
Perches, birdseed, hooting!

08:59.606 --> 09:02.407
It's not working!

09:02.442 --> 09:04.042
That weird
eye cloud again.

09:04.077 --> 09:07.011
This fall's taking longer
than I thought it would.

09:07.046 --> 09:09.013
I wish I had a game
to pass the time

09:09.048 --> 09:10.748
while we're plunging
to our death.

09:10.783 --> 09:12.717
Or, like, a puzzle
or something.

09:15.555 --> 09:17.556
A puzzle.

09:20.893 --> 09:24.696
So what if
I put this here?

09:24.731 --> 09:27.131
Um...

09:27.166 --> 09:30.235
¶¶

09:36.976 --> 09:38.977
Uh, who are you?

09:39.012 --> 09:42.380
Okay, you're some kind of
nightmare princess.

09:42.415 --> 09:44.783
But where are we?

09:45.585 --> 09:47.785
We're dead. I knew it.

09:47.820 --> 09:49.754
I'm guessing we're still asleep
on the boat.

09:49.789 --> 09:51.289
I think she entered
our nightmares

09:51.324 --> 09:54.058
and mashed them up in order
to communicate with us.

09:54.093 --> 09:55.961
What do you
want to tell us?

09:58.031 --> 09:59.230
Banana?

09:59.265 --> 10:02.801
[ Gasps ] She wants to hear
my banana story!

10:07.440 --> 10:08.573
[ All gasp ]

10:08.608 --> 10:10.875
She's harvesting
our mind-fruits!

10:12.679 --> 10:16.715
Wait, do you just want us to
give you some bananas?

10:17.950 --> 10:20.084
Well, there's loads on our boat.
You can take as many as you --

10:20.119 --> 10:22.920
No, Finn!
You have to negotiate first.

10:22.955 --> 10:24.989
We won't trade them
for anything less

10:25.024 --> 10:27.892
than something pretty
and/or cool.

10:32.632 --> 10:34.966
Enjoy those bananas!

10:37.136 --> 10:38.002
Pretty!

10:38.037 --> 10:40.138
What is this,
like, nightmare juice?

10:40.173 --> 10:41.906
Let's drink it!

10:44.644 --> 10:48.680
[ Yawns ] Hey,
look how close to home we are.

10:52.485 --> 10:54.485
Land ho!

10:54.520 --> 10:56.287
Hm.

10:56.322 --> 10:58.389
Mm-hmm.

10:58.424 --> 11:00.324
Yep.

11:00.359 --> 11:01.826
Ooh, la-la.

11:01.861 --> 11:03.628
How's it look, BMO?

11:03.663 --> 11:05.096
Like a dream.

11:07.266 --> 11:11.202
¶ Come along with me ¶

11:11.237 --> 11:15.740
¶ And the butterflies and bees ¶
